        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 17 at 5:19PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 519 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles southwest of Converse, or 23 miles south of Mansfield, moving
southwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Noble and Toledo Bend Reservoir North.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
